SIMPLE: immortal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immortal
<hw>Im*mor"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immortalis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>mortalis</ets>
mortal: cf. F. <ets>immortel</ets>. See <er>Mortal</er>, and cf.
<er>Immortelle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not mortal; exempt from
liability to die; undying; imperishable; lasting forever; having
unlimited, or eternal, existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unto the King eternal, <qex>immortal</qex>, invisible.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Tim. i. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For my soul, what can it do to that,⟦br⟧
Being a thing <qex>immortal</qex> as itself?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Connected with, or pertaining to
immortality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have <qex>immortal</qex> longings in me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Destined to live in all ages of this world; abiding;
exempt from oblivion; imperishable; <as>as, <ex>immortal</ex>
fame</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One of the few, <qex>immortal</qex> names,⟦br⟧
That were not born to die.</q> <rj><qau>Halleck.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Great; excessive; grievous.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hayward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Immortal flowers</b></col>, <cd>immortelles;
everlastings.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Eternal; everlasting; never-ending; ceaseless;
perpetual; continual; enduring; endless; imperishable; incorruptible;
deathless; undying.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immortal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Immortal
<hw>Im*mor"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who will never
cease to be; one exempt from death, decay, or annihilation.</def>
<rj><au>Bunyan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immortalist</ent>⟦br⟧
